data.title: Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine Winners
data.meta_description: Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine Winners - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or view presentation slides online. The document lists the winners of the Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine from 1901 to 2015. It provides the names of the laureates and the year they received the prize for their contributions to physiology and medicine. Notable prizes included those awarded to Ivan Pavlov in 1904 for his work on the physiology of digestion, to Frederick Banting and John Macleod in 1923 for the discovery of insulin and its use for diabetes treatment, and to James Watson, Francis Crick and Maurice Wilkins in 1962 for their discoveries regarding the molecular structure of nucleic acids and its significance for information transfer in living material.
